article.headline: Utah Valley State 57, UC Davis 38
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. (AP) -- Ryan Toolson scored 14 points Saturday as Utah Valley State dominated the second half to beat UC Davis 57-38. The Wolverines, who trailed 24-23 at halftime, held UC Davis to just 14 points on 6-for-25 shooting and allowed just two points over the final 7:52 of the game. Utah Valley State (10-5) has won four straight games. The Wolverines also grabbed 21 offensive rebounds that led to scoring opportunities yielding 16 points. Thomas Juillerat led UC Davis (2-11) with 11 points. The game was a matchup between schools that are ineligible for the postseason as they make the transition to Division I.
